definitions.definition: To evoke , educe (emotions, feelings, responses, etc.); to generate, obtain, or provoke as a response or answer.
To draw out , bring out , bring forth (something latent ); to obtain information from someone or something.
examples: Fred wished to elicit the time of the meeting from Jane.

definitions.definition: To use logic to arrive at truth ; to derive by reason.
